    "A total of 23 randomly selected cells were programmed into the LRS using the DC bias-sweep method, and the other cells were maintained in the initial state of the HRS.",
    "Subsequently, we verified the resistance state of each cell in the 8 × 8 CA under a reading voltage of 0.2 V and the corresponding one-third biasing scheme.",
    "Figure 6d shows the verified resistance state distribution of the 8 × 8 CA, which exhibits a resistance state distribution that is obviously different from that shown in Fig. 6c.",
    "While the extracted reading currents of the HRS and LRS from the unit cell in The programmed weight values of the CA were not coincident with the proposed programming scheme, indicating that programming and reading were not processed accurately owing to sneak current effects.",
